  <li id="comment-28362" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/18363454960621009448" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Janice</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/09/no-frosting-no-ceremony/#comment-28362"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-10-02T22:25:25-04:00">Sunday, October 2, 2011 at 10:25 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made the cake this morning and it is so so so good.  After saying that, I have to tell you that being lactose intolerant, and having issues with beet and cane sugars, I made a few substitutions.<br />Instead of the Golden syrup I used 100% maple syrup, instead of brown sugar I used maple sugar, instead of dairy milk I used plain soy milk, and instead of butter I used crisco&#8230;.  I know, I know, but, you know what, this is an amazing cake because even with all of those changes, it is awesome!  <br />The only thing I think I would do differently is maybe slice the plums into eighths instead of quarters, just to spread them more equally- and I don&#39;t think you could hurt this cake by putting in a couple extra plums either.  I&#39;m trying to figure out what I am going to do when the plums are gone.<br />Thanks for breakfast, lunch and dinner ðŸ™‚</p>
    </div>

